/span>  </span></span></span></div><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; font-family: &#039;PT Sans Caption&#039;, sans-serif; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.870588);\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: inherit;\">Although there is no fee to join, GLD Australia requests that its members also become and remain financial members of a gifted association or a learning disabilities association as they wish.</span></span></span></div><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; font-family: &#039;PT Sans Caption&#039;, sans-serif; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.870588);\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: inherit;\">This is run on an honour-system, but we’re confident that most GLD Australia members will comply with this request and will join whatever existing association they feel best suits their own needs.</span></span></span></div><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; font-family: &#039;PT Sans Caption&#039;, sans-serif; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.870588);\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"