);\"><a href=\"http://gfsg.org.au/articles/Published%20-%20Mindscape%20-%20teachers%20for%20GLD%20-%20what%20works%20-%20final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Mindscape - Teachers for GLD: What Works </a></p><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; font-family: &#039;PT Sans Caption&#039;, sans-serif; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.870588);\"> </div><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; font-family: &#039;PT Sans Caption&#039;, sans-serif; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.870588);\"> </div><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000; font-family: &#039;PT Sans Caption&#039;, sans-serif; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.870588);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: inherit;\">Questions?</span></span></span></strong></div><p><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Questions about any of the above are welcomed, and may be addressed to the GLD Australia national coordinator, Carol Barnes: <span id=\"cloak457bd357264f6768c156b1c5ecd91b09\"><a href=\"mailto:carol@bartink.com.au\">carol@bartink.com.au</a></span></span></span></p>',NULL,NULL,1,1,16,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',32),(185,38,3,1,3,3,'Page','2017-07-31 08:26:38','2017-07-28 11:42:36','media','Media',NULL,'<p>For all media requests please contact president@gfsg.org.au</p><p> </p><h1>Selective primaries an option but the gifted need more</h1><p>Melinda Gindy</p><p>Published: July 24 2017 - 12:05AM</p><p>On the weekend, the wider community heard a lot about what the NSW public school system could do for gifted children: better teacher training, an overhaul of the selective schools test and, perhaps most controversially, selective primary schools.</p><p>But unless you have a gifted child in your family or have taught one or were one, you probably don\'t know much about them. Gifted children think differently. They often approach problems in a more creative and divergent fashion than the majority of their age peers.</p><p>Please visit the <a href=\"http://www.smh.com.au/comment/selective-primaries-an-option-but-the-gifted-need-more-20170722-gxgos3.html\">Sydney Morning Herald</a> to read the full article.</p>',NULL,NULL,1,1,17,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',32),(186,26,6,1,3,3,'Page','2017-07-31 08:28:09','2017-07-28 10:55:08','little-gems','Little GEMs','Little GEMs Playgroup','<p><strong>Little GEMS is for children prior to school entry.</strong></p><p><br>GFSG Inc. hosts events and excursions where children can meet, play and explore together. Little GEMS have excursions and coffee and chat mornings throughout the terms.</p><p><br>Past excursions and coffee and chat mornings that have been held include: visits to Symbio Wildlife Park, Camellia Gardens, Menai High School Farm, Sydney Museum &amp; a Splash into incursion.</p><p>We have held many coffee and chat mornings and lunches around various venues in Sydney that are child friendly and provided opportunity for the children to play while the adults could engage in conversation relating to raising an often spirited gifted child.</p><p style=\"margin: 5px 0px; padding: 0px; color: #4d4d4d; font-family: &#039;Trebuchet MS&#039;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"> </p><p>For enquiries please contact <span id=\"cloak9f3f1f53055f42c6e61d9da546fc5923\"><a href=\"mailto:littlegems@gfsg.org.au\">littlegems@gfsg.org.au</a></span></p>',NULL,NULL,1,1,2,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',33),(187,21,7,1,3,3,'MembershipContainerPage','2017-07-31 08:52:22','2017-07-19 13:49:05','purchase-membership','Purchase Membership',NULL,'<p>GFSG Inc is a not for profit association designed to support families and teachers of gifted children. We do this through our K-8 games nights, Little GEMs Playgroup, School Holiday activities, Mum\'s Dinner\'s, Parent/teacher seminars, Facebook group for adults, Edmodo group for children, Member’s library, eNewsletters etc. We have built relationships with educators and professionals in Gifted Education field and have been able to incorporate their knowledge and experiences into the events and seminars we offer to our members and the wider community. We provide our members with up to date information and with the latest developments in gifted education. We have a library with an extensive range of books and resources available to full and professional members.</p><p>GFSG is affiliated with the Australian Association for the Education of the Gifted and Talented (AAEGT) and we represent NSW on the AAEGT Board of Directors. Through this affiliation, we are able to expand the support we give to our members by taking their concerns to a national level, as well as opening up new opportunities. All our members automatically become affiliated members of the AAEGT, with the option to subscribe to their biannual journal at members rates and to receive discounts to events hosted by other gifted associations.</p><p>GFSG membership also entitles you to join GLD Australia, a national online learning community responding to the needs of gifted children and adults with specific learning disabilities and challenges, and the needs of those who care for, teach and advocate for them, through the sharing of information, research and personal experiences. Membership in GLD Australia is free once you are a member of a gifted association such as GFSG. Should you wish to receive information on GLD Australia and how to join, please see a committee member or view the resources tab on this website.</p><h2><strong>Which membership is right for you?</strong></h2><p>There are 3 types of membership – Full membership, Professional membership and School Membership.</p><p>Please have a look at the types of membership offered to work out what will suit your family needs. If you are unsure, please contact our President, Melinda, at president@gfsg.org.au to discuss what is best for you.</p><p><strong>Full Membership</strong></p><p>$60 per family per year or $110 per family for 2 years (up to 2 adults and their children)</p><p>Entitles you to:</p><ul><li>Discounts on seminars, games night, excursions, ladies retreats and any other GFSG events</li>\n<li>Quarterly e-newsletter</li>\n<li>Email updates about seminars &amp; upcoming events</li>\n<li>Children can join the “GFSG Kids Edmodo group” for GFSG members only</li>\n<li>Parents/Caregivers (Mums &amp; Dads) can join the new private facebook support group</li>\n<li>Library – borrowing of books and other resources (Postage at member’s cost)</li>\n<li>Affiliated membership with AAEGT (affiliated annually on 31st May) plus the opportunity to receive the twice-yearly AAEGT journal at the discounted additional cost of $30 per year.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Professional Membership</strong></p><p>$30 per professional or teacher</p><p>Entitles you to:</p><ul><li>Discounts at seminars</li>\n<li>Quarterly e-newsletter</li>\n<li>Library – borrowing of books and other resources (Postage at member’s cost)</li>\n<li>Email updates about seminars &amp; upcoming events</li>\n<li>Affiliated membership with AAEGT (affiliated annually on 31st May) plus the opportunity to receive the twice-yearly AAEGT journal at the discounted additional cost of $30 per year.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>School Membership</strong></p><p>$80 per School per year</p><p>Entitles you to:</p><ul><li>Discounts at seminars (limited to 5 staff members per event)</li>\n<li>Quarterly e-newsletter</li>\n<li>Library – borrowing of books and other resources (Postage at school’s cost)</li>\n<li>Email updates about seminars &amp; upcoming events</li>\n<li>Affiliated membership with AAEGT (affiliated annually on 31st May) plus the opportunity to receive the twice-yearly AAEGT journal at the discounted additional cost of $30 per year.</li>\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,1,1,3,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',13),(188,21,8,1,3,3,'MembershipContainerPage','2017-07-31 08:53:15','2017-07-19 13:49:05','purchase-membership','Purchase Membership',NULL,'<p>GFSG Inc is a not for profit association designed to support families and teachers of gifted children. We do this through our K-8 games nights, Little GEMs Playgroup, School Holiday activities, Mum\'s Dinner\'s, Parent/teacher seminars, Facebook group for adults, Edmodo group for children, Member’s library, eNewsletters etc. We have built relationships with educators and professionals in Gifted Education field and have been able to incorporate their knowledge and experiences into the events and seminars we offer to our members and the wider community. We provide our members with up to date information and with the latest developments in gifted education. We have a library with an extensive range of books and resources available to full and professional members.</p><p>GFSG is affiliated with the Australian Association for the Education of the Gifted and Talented (AAEGT) and we represent NSW on the AAEGT Board of Directors. Through this affiliation, we are able to expand the support we give to our members by taking their concerns to a national level, as well as opening up new opportunities. All our members automatically become affiliated members of the AAEGT, with the option to subscribe to their biannual journal at members rates and to receive discounts to events hosted by other gifted associations.</p><p>GFSG membership also entitles you to join GLD Australia, a national online learning community responding to the needs of gifted children and adults with specific learning disabilities and challenges, and the needs of those who care for, teach and advocate for them, through the sharing of information, research and personal experiences. Membership in GLD Australia is free once you are a member of a gifted association such as GFSG. Should you wish to receive information on GLD Australia and how to join, please see a committee member or view the resources tab on this website.</p><h2><strong>Choose your membership<br></strong></h2><p>Please have a look at the types of membership offered to work out what will suit your family needs. If you are unsure, please contact our President, Melinda, at president@gfsg.org.au to discuss what is best for you.</p>',NULL,NULL,1,1,3,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',13),(189,31,5,1,3,3,'Page','2017-07-31 09:01:45','2017-07-28 10:58:55','kids-corner','Kid\'s Corner',NULL,'<h2>Pen and Paper Challenges</h2><p>Members can join the discussion in Edmodo (please login to access this resource).</p><p><strong>Puzzle 1:</strong></p><p><strong><img class=\"leftAlone\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/ResizedImageWzYwMCw0MzVd/Puzzle-20170716.png\" alt=\"Puzzle 20170716\" width=\"600\" height=\"435\"></strong></p><p> </p><p>What number belongs in place of the ?</p><p><strong>St Ives Riddle:</strong></p><p>As I was going to St Ives, I met a man with seven wives.  Each wife had seven sacks. Each sack held seven cats.  Each cat had seven kittens. Kittens, cats, sacks and wives, how many were going to St Ives?</p><ol><li