iding a vast array of supportive events and highlighting the needs of gifted children within our community.</p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">GFSG Inc. is affiliated with the Australian Association for the Education of Gifted and Talented Children (AAEGT) and represents NSW on the AAEGT Board. Through this affiliation, GFSG Inc. is able to expand the support we give to our members by taking their concerns to a national level and open up new opportunities. All our members automatically become members of the AAEGT, with options to subscribe to their biannual journal at members rates, and to receive discounts to events hosted by other gifted associations.</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">GFSG Inc. is also affiliated with GLD Australia; a national online learning community responding to the needs of gifted children and gifted adults with specific learning disability and other learning challenges.</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">To attend a GFSG Inc. event, children are not required to sit an IQ test.  Given our current website upgrade, it may be easiest to view the events calendar, including South-Coast Sub Branch events, here: <a title=\"Updated 31 July 2017\" href=\"[file_link,id=8]\">EVENTS CALENDAR July-Dec 2017.</a>  (Be sure to check regularly for updates and changes.)  Be sure to also check out the \"news and events\" section below for our upcoming celebrations, and the \"sub branch\" tab above for more from the south coast!</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">GFSG Inc. is a place where we hope you can feel ‘at home’ in a world where our children often seem the ‘odd ones out’.</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Melinda Gindy- President of GFSG Inc.</span></p>',NULL,NULL,1,1,1,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',0),(215,53,5,1,3,3,'MerchandiseContainerPage','2017-08-13 20:47:46','2017-08-09 10:39:38','gfsg-merchandise','Merchandise',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,5,0,0,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',13),(216,42,3,1,3,3,'Page','2017-08-13 20:49:53','2017-07-28 12:08:27','library','Library',NULL,'<p>GFSG Inc. have a library which includes a broad range of books, journals and CD’s that are relevant to professionals and parents on the subjects of giftedness and twice exceptionality. There are also books for children.</p><p>Borrowing is available at GFSG Inc. events for GFSG Inc. members including <a href=\"[sitetree_link,id=25]\">Games for Enquiring Minds</a>. 1 item can be borrowed per member and borrowing period is for one month. Items can be returned to a GFSG event or can be mailed to: PO Box 604 Moorebank NSW, 1875. When items are borrowed, record details of member and books. If items have not been returned 6 weeks after borrowing, the member will be contacted and borrowing privileges will be suspended until items are returned.</p>',NULL,NULL,1,1,2,0,0,NULL,'OnlyTheseUsers','Inherit',13),(217,44,4,1,3,3,'Page','2017-08-13 20:50:20','2017-07-28 12:26:50','edmodo','Edmodo',NULL,'<p><span style=\"color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\"><img class=\"leftAlone\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/ResizedImageWzYwMCwxNjRd/Edmodo.png\" alt=\"Edmodo\" width=\"600\" height=\"164\"></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\">Have your children joined the GFSG members only</span><span style=\"color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\"> </span><span class=\"highlightNode\" style=\"border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgba(88, 144, 255, 0.298039); padding: 0px 1px; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgba(88, 144, 255, 0.14902);\">Edmodo</span><span style=\"color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\"> group?</span></p><p><span style=